<br>
I've previously responded to reported feelings of Ted Taylor, that he supposedly was still favorably inclined to consider a peaceful application of bomb technology in space travel.<br>
 He said something like (anybody feel free to supply the exact quote, reported by G.Dyson) that when you look at the pandora's box which is nuclear energy technology, all these horrible things are immediately apparent. We just have to refuse to consider them.<br>
 If we dig a little deeper into the box, we see -down near the bottom perhaps- the really significant contents of the box which is hope.<br>
 We have to discipline ourselves to use the hope, and refuse the horror. There still is hope for disentangling nuclear power technologies from the horror of Hiroshima. (It's called Orion)<br>
