<br>
I see lots of people who say this, and I agree, but after long thought I believe there is more to it than that.<br>
<br>
Let me explain.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Several times I have mentioned that large NTR powered boosters could drive a paradigm shift in how space access is perceived.  What I mean by this is more than simple cheap access.<br>
<br>
Cheap access could be achieved using light-gas guns to simply shoot payload to orbit.  Cheap access could be achieved by using hydrogen balloons to loft ramrocket miniplanes that then launch microrockets into orbit, each one carrying a teaspoon into orbit for a pittance.<br>
<br>
But those cheap methods are not going to fire anybody's imagination.  <br>
<br>
The way to space needs to be BIG, human scaled or larger.  It needs to be grand, and stately, and proud, and worthy of admiration.<br>
<br>
A semi-truck is not graceful, but it certainly garners respect and a certain admiration.  We need that sort of a system to get to space.<br>
<br>
Chemical fuels just can't do it.  People can tell when a system is barely scraping by.  Nobody buys a car that has been engineered to the last iota of efficiency.  (At least not in any huge numbers.)  People buy cars because the doors sound solid and it accelerates good.  Silly, isn't it?<br>
<br>
People like knowing their machines are capable and strong, more than adequate to the task at hand.  Chemical fuels make that extra margin impossible, so people are leery of them.<br>
<br>
I feel that THAT is the paradigm shift we need to achieve if the general public is going to get behind space in a serious way.<br>
<br>
Does that make any sense to anyone?<br>
<br>
An Orion type design would fulfill this sort of a paradigm shift, but frankly, I think we can do a better and more efficient job these days.  I have laid out the basic blocks of a system that could do this, using todays tech.  I think I'll call it the  Two Stage to Solar System system.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
